components.name: Stoddard Solvent
components.notes: MSDSs for three products listed "mineral spirit" with the CAS number for Stoddard solvent.  Mineral spirit is a synonym for Stoddard, so we counted these sources as examples of Stoddard's use in asphalt dampproofing products.. Water is a less common solvent alternative

environmental.systemBoundary: The system boundary includes the ingredients, transportation of those ingredients to a mixing facility, and the heating of the bitumen. The petroleum ingredients are assumed to be sourced from regional refineries and transported via truck; the attapulgite is sourced from Georgia and travels cross-country via rail. Mixing of the ingredients is estimated based on the heating value of bitumen and the accompanying combustion of natural gas.
environmental.endOfLifeTreatment: All material is sent to the landfill and assumed to be inert.

name: Foundation dampproofing
description: Dampproofing products are typically asphalt-based and applied to the exterior of a foundation to prevent moisture from migrating out of the ground and into the pores of the concrete or masonry.  Many products recommend two coats be applied, either by brush or spray, 24 hours apart.
